  <refnamediv>
    <refname>semicolon (;)</refname>
    <refpurpose>ending expression and row separator</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
    semicolons are used to separate rows in a matrix definition (within brackets).</para>
    <para>
    semicolons may also be used at the end of an instruction (in a file or in Scilab console). In this
    case it means that the result(s) is(are) not displayed. Conversely use
    comma (,) to get the display.</para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Examples</title>
    <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
    a=[1,2,3;4,5,6];
    a=1;b=1,c=2
    ]]></programlisting>
  </refsection>
